Aug 13 2009 	Beautiful Hotel and Great Location!	I did a lot of research before settling on the Sheraton Dubai Creek Hotel and Towers. We were very happy with our stay. It is just a short taxi ride from the airport. The rooms were beautifully decorated and there is a nice variety of restaurants in the hotel. We were going to swim one night but the extreme humidity outside made it a bit miserable so we passed on that. But the pool area is nice. The only complaint we had was they charged for WIFI...these days, come on...free WIFI is being given at the cheapest hotels around, I didn't understand it. Also, the bathroom door was designed to slam shut, you couldn't keep it open when you got ready, therefore you had to stand in a steamy bathroom...that isn't too bad of a complaint though, we jammed towels under the door to remedy this! It is located in a great area right on the Dubai Creek. We had a blast taking the water taxi (Abra) to the other side of the creek and exploring the area. The Abra is a short walk from the hotel. There is a non-airconditioned Abra for 1 dir or an air conditioned one for slightly more...take the A/C one if it's hot. On the other side of the creek is the Dubai Museum. Really great! And lots of shopping too. We were happy with our stay and paid under $90 a night booking directly from the hotel's website. I think it was a special summer deal! Great place to stay!	
