Oct 28 2008 	Perfect to see the real Dubai	Like many others, I spent about 6 weeks agonising over different reviews and trying to work out what to do: stay in the city, stay at the beach, etc. I couldn't have been happier with my decision. The hotel was a good 5-star hotel standard that you'd expect from any major city. Top quality without the mega-luxury you'd pay three times for. If you want to lay in the sun all day and spend a tonne on room service (and do nothing much else), then stay at the big resorts near the beach. However you can lay in the sun anywhere (and in much cheaper resorts with better beaches!). I recommend staying at this hotel and then you're only a stroll from the creek (creek is an understatement), the souks, the musuem, the river cruises and the open top bus tours (5 mins away). Although don't expect everything at your immediate doorstep - I'm a happy walker and all the above was within a 5-20 minute walk. I went past the beach front resorts on the bus tour and they seemed to be out in the middle of nowhere - you'd have to get a cab to go anywhere. Not my idea of a cultural experience! But each to their own. I was disappointed with the shopping malls - they're just shopping malls! Go to the souks and museum instead. Also highly recommend making a dinner reservation at the italian restaurant in the hotel - just remember to ask for a table on the non-smoking balcony. The breakfast was brilliant. The english style pub was a little disappointing - better to get room service! The hotel was very accommodating with my early arrival time too - they let me sleep out on a sun lounge near the pool (which was also very nice btw) for a little while, and then I ended up getting checked in early by about 1030am. Even got upgraded to a club room on the corner which was awesome. I wouldn't stay anywhere else if I went back. PS - yes, it is worth it to pay extra for a creek view room.	
