Jun 9 2008 	Good stay but there's better out there	Stayed for 3 nights during Oct 2007.Overall, the hotel is comfortable and clean. However, I was not blown away by any aspect of my stay. Check in was fast and our room had a great creek view.The location is perhaps not suited to most tourist's tastes. You will need to get a taxi to most places, however, they are not expensive. If I ever visit Dubai again (although probably not, as there's nothing much to see or do), I would probably opt for a hotel on the beach side. Breakfast at the Sheraton was ok. The selection was adequate and there is a very nice balcony to sit at.As I visited Dubai in the holy month of Ramadan, no food or drink was allowed to be consumed at the pool area, and eating places everywhere were screened off so as not to offend those following the traditions of Ramadan. some bars and restaurants were also closed in other hotels we visited during our trip. This is something to bear in mind if you are travelling at this time. In short, the Sheraton Creek side is an good hotel but nothing spectacular.	
May 30 2008 	Loved the Sheraton and Thomas!	I traveled with 3 other women last week, and stayed at the Sheraton Dubai Creek for 7 nights. I truly appreciated the kindness of everyone on staff, including Thomas, who as you can tell from his review responses, cares more about his hotel than any other manager I've ever seen. The rooms were lovely and clean, and the quality of the food in the hotel was not something I often see at hotels in the states. Our room was 107 and overlooked the creek, which had amazing views. I also loved all the gorgeous, unique flower arrangements around the hotel.I had 2 jet-lag massages while I was there, and they were wonderful and very well priced. For 80 minutes, it was about $90 which is a steal if you've priced other resort spas. The pool was wonderful, as the chairs are all padded lounge chairs and there's plenty of shaded areas to sit. The hotel also arranged for our Arabian Adventures tour, which was a real treat. We never had a problem getting a taxi, which are very inexpensive. The Sheraton is a short drive from just about every destination you'd wish to visit, but really you don't have to leave the hotel if you don't feel like it, as there are Italian, Indian, and Japanese restaurants, not to mention the pub, a pastry bar, and a mid-day mini-gourmet buffet in the lobby.I want to go back already! Thank you, Thomas for such a wonderful stay.	
