Oct 28 2007	Good value (for Dubai)	In a city of exceptionally expensive hotels, the Sheraton Dubai Creek Hotel &amp; Towers offers decent value for five star accommodation.The hotel room was clean and comfortable. A room with a view of the Creek, towards the new city is very pleasant. The hotel facilities (gym and pool) were of a high standard.Hotel food was excellent.The service was excellent in parts (front desk, restaurants, concierge) and shocking in others (&quot;Towers&quot; lounge).The hotel location is mixed - it really depends what you want to do. If you're a tourist, it's OK but expect to give yourself an hour to get to Mall of the Emirates, Burj Al Arab, Madinat, Jumeirah Beach Hotel etc. If you're on business, the location is a bit of a pain - give yourself a good 30 minutes to get to Jumeirah Emirates Towers or DIFC.It's a good location for the airport (15 minutes), the Gold Souk, and Burj Dubai. It's pretty easy to get a taxi, and the folks at the hotel are more than happy to provide you with detailed directions if you want to catch a boat somewhere (at the rear of the hotel). A few other points about this hotel:1. I noticed that the hotel website makes a distinction between standard rooms and &quot;towers&quot; rooms. I was always under the impression that a &quot;towers&quot; room was something special. However, when I arrived at the hotel I discovered that almost all rooms are &quot;towers&quot; rooms. A bit of marketing puffery, I think!2. The hotel tries to sting you real bad for trying to check-in early - watch out! In my case, they did allow me to check out at 3PM, and store my luggage, and use the health club to shower before taking a late flight.3. If you do check-out, dont try to go into the &quot;towers&quot; lounge, they attempt to charge you for having a drink and a piece of fruit.4. The hotel booking process was very annoying - five emails to get a &quot;towers&quot; room with two beds and early check-in!Overall, I think the hotel offers good value but I would try somewhere else next time.	
