May 3 2006	Amazing Views and Great Location	We stayed at the Sheraton in August 2005 for our Honeymoon for 4 nights. This was not long enough!We had a Creek view with amazing views and would definately reecommend upgrading to one of these rooms.We chose a room away from the beach purposly, so that we could visit the city easily. There is a shuttle service to the sister Sheraton on the beach however, which is also well worth a visit.The hotel has a range of restaurants from Indian to Italian. The Indian was especially good. There is evening entertainment with a singer and pianist, but nothing to get excited over. The Creek diner is well worth a try though, a romantic trip along the Creek at night with buffet and belly dancer.The hotel staff are efficient and cater for your needs, even if they do it without the most enthuiasum.Rooms have floor to ceiling glass looking out to the Creek, air conditioning which works and is definately needed as you can feel the heat if you stand next to the window. There are slippers, tv, video, hi fi, fridge, king size bed, desk, sofa - everything you need whilst taking a break from the heat.The entrance/lobby of the hotel along with the the Creek views are what stands out from our stay in the Sheraton Dubai Creek.We would definately recommend it and will be going back this year!!	
Apr 26 2006	Fabulous hotel in a great location	We arrived at The Sheraton Dubai Creek at 3.00.a.m. very tired but excited for our first visit to Dubai. Our first impressions of the hotel were that it was absolutely stunning - the foyer was enormous and once up the escalators, we were transported into a world of luxury and opulence. The reception area was welcoming and inviting - we were offered iced orange juice whilst the receptionist took down our details: this obviously impressed us too!As we were celebrating our wedding anniversary we were even more delighted to find a huge chocolate cake bearing 'Congratulations' awaiting us in our room. We didn't have a Creek view room, but still our room was lovely and spacious, with everything we needed.Breakfasts were to die for - we have never seen a choice like it, in all the hotels we have stayed in, and we spent at least one hour over this, sitting outside on the terrace, overlooking the Creek. Bliss!The hotel's location suited us down to the ground - we purposely did not choose a beach resort because we wanted to see the hub of the city - and we were able to walk to the souks along the hustle and bustle of the creekside, watching the men loading and unloading their cargoes onto the old wooden dhows.Recommended sights to see - Big Bus Tour which takes you absolutely everywhere, desert safari in the white knuckle 4x4 Toyota Landcruisers, complete with camel ride and belly dancer, relaxing by the hotel pool (small but beautifully kept and clean), evening dinner cruise on the Creek.We had a fantastic time in Dubai, made all the better for our stay at The Sheraton Dubai Creek - we cannot recommend it more highly.	
